      "content": "I can't advise you to take medication that's not prescribed for you. If you're concerned about the chest tightness and nausea, talking to your doctor or therapist in the morning might be the best option. They can assess your symptoms and provide guidance on how to manage them properly. Taking a half dose of diazepam without consulting your doctor can be unpredictable and may worsen your symptoms or interact with other medications you're taking.",
